Package de.rwth.i2.attestor.graph.heap

All abstractions needed to work with HeapConfigurations.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    HeapConfiguration
    A HeapConfiguration is a hypergraph in which each node corresponds to a location on the heap of a program, such as null or a reference to some object.
    HeapConfigurationBuilder
    A HeapConfigurationBuilder allows to mutate a given HeapConfiguration.
    HeapConfigurationExporter
    A general method to export HeapConfigurations in a format that has to be specified by implementations.
    Matching
    A Matching models a mapping from one HeapConfiguration, called the pattern HeapConfiguration, to another HeapConfiguration, called the target HeapConfiguration.
    NonterminalEdgeBuilder  
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Variable
    Wrapper for a String such that Strings can be used as NodeLabel in LabeledDigraph.
